title: Merge pull request #510 from sussol/#xxx-persist-last-sync-time
message:
Merge pull request #510 from sussol/#xxx-persist-last-sync-time

Use redux persist to remember last sync time and any error

title: Use redux persist to remember last sync time and any error
message:
Use redux persist to remember last sync time and any error

Note: not using autoRehydrate, so that this is an ‘opt-in’ system,
where a reducer must provide the REHYDRATE action in order to have some
part of state persisted. This is to avoid redux-persist unexpectedly
remembering too much (e.g. we don’t want navigation persisted)

title: Fixes the mSupplyMobileApp constructing again on reopen
message:
Fixes the mSupplyMobileApp constructing again on reopen

Have had a bug whereby if you press the ‘home’ button, but don’t
actually kill the app, then you reopen the app by tapping its icon, the
currentUser gets set to null (among other things that happen during the
MSupplyMobileApp constructor). This was bound to cause some nasty
issues, and is fixed by this change.

title: Change inter store requisition interface design
message:
Change inter store requisition interface design

Major changes:
- Separated customer and supplier requisitions into pages with buttons
in appropriate sections of the menu
- Customer invoice no longer created automatically on syncing in a
response requisition
- Customer invoice created (and finalised) on finalising response
requisition

And fix a few things along the way:
- Add customer invoice number to customer requisition info section
- Change ‘Supplying Store’ to customer in customer requisition info
section
- Fix date formatting in ‘Entered Date’ everywhere
- Remove unhelpful ‘Entered By’ on both type of requisition
- Changed finalise message to be different for customer and supplier
requisitions

Still to do:
- Write a finaliseCheck for customer requisitions
- Work out why otherStoreName is missing
- Testing

title: Prevent crashes when deleting rows of data
message:
Prevent crashes when deleting rows of data

* Fixes #348
* I believe an update to react native that removed some of the
shouldComponentUpdate rules means that the datatable is now updating
directly after setState({ selection: [] }), and before the refreshData
is called, resulting in it trying to render a deleted record
* Could call refreshData prior to the setState, but would need to call
it again immediately after, so seems a bit excessive
* This way also prevents future bugs
